[snowflake-sync] use original column case when executing DDL
*What this PR does / why we need it:*
In Snowflake, it is impossible to quote an identifier (e.g. a column name) without knowing its case, as the quoted identifiers "mycolumn" and "MYCOLUMN" are different, as Snowflake is case sensitive. As such, in order for us to be able to safely add in quoting (to handle special characters), we also need to know the original column case.
Fortunately, this is stored as table properties in the Okera table. This change leverages that to compute that mapping and then leverage it whenever we need to get the original column case (e.g. when setting/unsetting column masking policies).
There's likely some other places in the DDL we generate that require this, but that can be done in a future change.
*Special notes for your reviewer:*
*Additional testing that was done:*
ADDITIONAL_CI_TESTS:
``` Release note: ```
Change-Id: I82cde3307926268200431ccebce87a2ec27f747c
